concept_set_name: [HCUP] Other specified and unspecified lower respiratory disease
concept_set_version_title: [HCUP] Other specified and unspecified lower respiratory disease (v1)
comments: Exported from VSAC and bulk imported to N3C.
intention: ICD-10-CM Body System (largely aligned with ICD-10-CM chapters) diseases of the respiratory system. RSP contains 17 categories that include diseases of the respiratory system such a as influenza, asthma, acute bronchitis, and pneumothorax.
limitations: The grouping is based on Clinical Classifications Software Refines (CCSR). The CCSR for ICD-10-CM provides a method for aggregating the diagnosis codes into over 530 clinical categories across 21 body systems.  For more information about the CCSR: https://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/toolssoftware/ccsr/DXCCSR-User-Guide-v2022-1.pdf
provenance: AHRQ National Inpatient Sample, Healthcare Cost & Utilization Project (HCUP), 2019, CCSR RSP016; CSSR Code: RSP016

BLD contains 10 categories that include diseases related to the blood, diseases of blood-forming organs, and certain disorders involving the immune mechanism such as nutritional anemia, sickle cell/trait anemia, and immunity disorders.
limitations: The grouping is based on Clinical Classifications Software Refines (CCSR). The CCSR for ICD-10-CM provides a method for aggregating the diagnosis codes into over 530 clinical categories across 21 body systems.  For more information about the CCSR: https://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/toolssoftware/ccsr/DXCCSR-User-Guide-v2022-1.pdf
provenance: AHRQ National Inpatient Sample, Healthcare Cost & Utilization Project (HCUP), 2019, CCSR BLD007; CSSR Code: BLD007

limitations: The grouping is based on Clinical Classifications Software Refines (CCSR). The CCSR for ICD-10-CM provides a method for aggregating the diagnosis codes into over 530 clinical categories across 21 body systems.  For more information about the CCSR: https://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/toolssoftware/ccsr/DXCCSR-User-Guide-v2022-1.pdf
provenance: AHRQ National Inpatient Sample, Healthcare Cost & Utilization Project (HCUP), 2019, CCSR BLD008; CSSR Code: BLD008

MBD contains 32 categories that include mental, behavioral, and neurodevelopmental disorders such as depressive disorders, alcohol-related disorders, and suicide ideation/ attempt/ intentional self-harm.
limitations: The grouping is based on Clinical Classifications Software Refines (CCSR). The CCSR for ICD-10-CM provides a method for aggregating the diagnosis codes into over 530 clinical categories across 21 body systems.  For more information about the CCSR: https://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/toolssoftware/ccsr/DXCCSR-User-Guide-v2022-1.pdf
provenance: AHRQ National Inpatient Sample, Healthcare Cost & Utilization Project (HCUP), 2019, CCSR MBD024; CSSR Code: MBD024

MBD contains 32 categories that include mental, behavioral, and neurodevelopmental disorders such as depressive disorders, alcohol-related disorders, and suicide ideation/ attempt/ intentional self-harm.
limitations: The grouping is based on Clinical Classifications Software Refines (CCSR). The CCSR for ICD-10-CM provides a method for aggregating the diagnosis codes into over 530 clinical categories across 21 body systems.  For more information about the CCSR: https://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/toolssoftware/ccsr/DXCCSR-User-Guide-v2022-1.pdf
provenance: AHRQ National Inpatient Sample, Healthcare Cost & Utilization Project (HCUP), 2019, CCSR MBD003; CSSR Code: MBD003
